From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] scsi: quirk FRMW MicroSD(2nd Gen) media change

Opt the configured removable reader into the narrowly scoped media-change
resume handling. Keep SKIP_IO_HINTS because an exact devinfo match replaces
the transport-provided flags during SCSI scan.

The reader is treated as fixed media for UNIT ATTENTION 28/00 and must not
have its card removed or replaced while the system is running or suspended.

---
diff --git a/drivers/scsi/scsi_devinfo.c b/drivers/scsi/scsi_devinfo.c
--- a/drivers/scsi/scsi_devinfo.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/scsi_devinfo.c
@@ -166,6 +166,9 @@ static struct {
 	{"easyRAID", "16P", NULL, BLIST_NOREPORTLUN},
 	{"easyRAID", "X6P", NULL, BLIST_NOREPORTLUN},
 	{"easyRAID", "F8", NULL, BLIST_NOREPORTLUN},
+	{"FRMW", "MicroSD(2nd Gen)", NULL,
+	 BLIST_IGN_MEDIA_CHANGE | BLIST_INQUIRY_36 |
+	 BLIST_SKIP_IO_HINTS | BLIST_RETRY_MEDIA_CHANGE},
 	{"FSC", "CentricStor", "*", BLIST_SPARSELUN | BLIST_LARGELUN},
 	{"FUJITSU", "ETERNUS_DXM", "*", BLIST_RETRY_ASC_C1},
 	{"Generic", "USB SD Reader", "1.00", BLIST_FORCELUN | BLIST_INQUIRY_36},
